title: Woman of My Dreams - Sass; wav file
description:
This is a dithered 16bit / 44.1kHz file of the final mix. The .mp3 that is also on this site was made from this. I also have a 24bit,  full rhythm track with no vocals and no fade, if anyone&#039;s interested.

Woman of My Dreams by Sass

Written and performed by Andy Andro Ernst and Sass.
Andy Ernst is a music producer and engineer who has worked with bands such as Green Day, Rancid and AFI. Most of his work is done with punk rock bands. - Wikipedia

Song recorded at Golden State Recorders San Francisco, CA in August 1979 by David Buell and the students of The College of Recording Arts.

16 track 2 inch tape restored and transfered to digital by Sonicraft, Inc. and then remixed by David Buell in November of 2007.

Play loud & enjoy!
